      <originalsloc id="aspace_e64ed371d9bbfabe2545d3b3967596b2">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection can be located in the Dean Gooderham Acheson Papers (MS 1087).   The papers include correspondence, writings, speeches, memoranda, and photographs, documenting Dean Acheson's life after leaving the U.S. State Department in 1953. Also documented is his work as a member of the Yale Corporation and his long friendship with Felix Frankfurter, Archibald MacLeish, and others.</p>
         <p>HM 258 consists of the entire collection, with the exception of Box 56 and restricted files from the main accession and Accessions 1983-M-005, 1985-M-015, 1991-M-065, 2003-M-050, and 2003-M-075.</p>
         <p>Please note: Selected correspondence is also reproduced in Among Friends, edited by David Acheson and David McClellan, New York: Dodd, Mead, 1980.</p>  
      </originalsloc>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_bcf03d6dee16933696dc6fe96b1c57ab">
